ISW (Infi Systems Widgets) - XCB-based 3D Widget Library
==========================================================

ISW is a modern fork of the X 3D Athena Widget Set (Xaw3d).

##WARNING
It was majority done by claude code after the initial work on libXt to support XCB.

HERE BE (COPIOUS AMOUNTS) OF DRAGONS.

If anyone is willing to do manual review of the LLM output that would be very appreciated

##ENDWARNING

This library provides a comprehensive set of widgets for building X11 graphical
user interfaces, with a complete XCB-based implementation that eliminates all
Xlib dependencies.

FEATURES
--------
- Modern XCB rendering backend for better performance and smaller footprint
- Complete X Toolkit Intrinsics (libXt) implementation using XCB
- Single unified library (libISW.so) includes both widgets and toolkit
- No Xlib dependencies - pure XCB implementation

ARCHITECTURE
------------
ISW is a self-contained widget toolkit that includes:
  - ISW Widgets: Full set of 3D Athena widgets (Box, Button, List, Text, etc.)
  - X Toolkit Intrinsics: XCB-based reimplementation of the Xt library
  - XCB Integration: Direct X11 protocol communication via XCB

All components are built into a single libISW.so library with no external
dependencies on traditional Xlib or libXt.

BUILDING
--------
See BUILD_INSTRUCTIONS.md for detailed build instructions.

Quick start:
    ./autogen.sh
    ./configure --enable-arrow-scrollbars --enable-internationalization
    make
    sudo make install

DEPENDENCIES
------------
Required build dependencies:
  - libxcb and XCB extension libraries (xfixes, render, shape, xrm, keysyms)
  - libxft (Freetype-based font rendering)
  - libsm, libice (X Session Management)
  - bison, flex (for parser generation)
  - Standard build tools (gcc, autoconf, automake, libtool, pkg-config)

USAGE
-----
Programs using ISW can link against it using pkg-config:

    gcc myapp.c -o myapp $(pkg-config --cflags --libs isw)

Example code:
    #include <X11/Intrinsic.h>
    #include <X11/StringDefs.h>
    #include <ISW/Box.h>
    #include <ISW/Command.h>

    int main(int argc, char **argv)
    {
        Widget toplevel, box, button;
        
        toplevel = XtInitialize(argv[0], "MyApp", NULL, 0, &argc, argv);
        box = XtCreateManagedWidget("box", boxWidgetClass, toplevel, NULL, 0);
        button = XtCreateManagedWidget("quit", commandWidgetClass, box, NULL, 0);
        
        XtRealizeWidget(toplevel);
        XtMainLoop();
        
        return 0;
    }

FORKED FROM
-----------
This project is an attempt at a modern fork of Xaw3d (X 3D Athena Widget Set).


Original Xaw3d repository:
    git://anongit.freedesktop.org/git/xorg/lib/libXaw3d

